rred Stock at **$75.46/share** (initial price per share for Series E).\n- This converted into **3.8 million shares of SpaceX Class A Common Stock** (pre-split basis) following the merger.\n\n---\n\n## 7. xAI Merger Consideration\n\n- SpaceX issued **321.7 million Class A shares**, **121.7 million Class B shares**, and **$2,947 million in cash** to xAI holders as merger consideration.\n- xAI Series A-1 through E preferred stock converted at **0.1433 shares of SpaceX Class A common per preferred share** (pre-split).\n- xAI Series A (high-vote) converted at **0.1433 shares of SpaceX Class B common per preferred share** (pre-split).\n- Eligible service providers could elect **$75.46 cash per share** of xAI Series A preferred instead of stock.\n\n---\n\n## 8. What Is NOT Present\n\nImportantly, the excerpts **do not contain**:\n- Explicit secondary market pricing data (e.g., tender offers, broker-dealer quotes)\n- Fair value estimates from independent valuations (e.g., 409A valuations)\n- Post-merger enterprise or equity valuation of the combined entity\n- IPO price range or implied market capitalization (these appear redacted as "blank" fields: `$______`)\n- Any discussion of pre-IPO valuation benchmarks or comparable company multiples\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThe document provides **negotiated financing-round prices** (from $1 to $270/share for SpaceX, $1 to $75.46/share for xAI), **implied secondary market prices from repurchase transactions** ($18–$95/share for SpaceX common), and **aggregate carrying values** (~$7.1B for SpaceX preferred, ~$31.7B for xAI preferred, ~$38.8B combined). The actual IPO pricing and market capitalization figures appear to be intentionally left blank in this version of the prospectus.',
