nificant buybacks of both Common and Preferred Stock. The **$1,021 million** total ($920M Common + $101M Preferred) represents open-market activity with employees and shareholders.\n*   **2025:** Repurchases continued, though at a lower volume for SpaceX Common Stock. A notable new transaction was the **$600 million** purchase of **xAI Common Stock**, which later became a repurchase in the consolidated statements following the xAI Merger.\n*   **Key Condition:** The company only repurchased shares held by eligible participants for more than six months, at a purchase price equal to the **then-current fair market value**.\n\n#### 2. Quarterly Repurchases (Early 2025 & 2026)\n\n*   **Q1 2025:** The repurchase program remained active with **$508 million** spent on SpaceX Common Stock.\n*   **Q1 2026:** This quarter saw two distinct, large-scale repurchase programs:\n    *   **xAI Merger Buyback ($2,413 million):** A direct consequence of the xAI business combination, this transaction repurchased shares from eligible current and former xAI employees.\n    *   **Open-Market Transactions ($1,933 million):** SpaceX repurchased additional shares of its own Common and Preferred Stock from existing shareholders at fair market value.\n\n#### 3. Retirement of Shares\n\n*   **All SpaceX shares repurchased to date have been retired.**\n*   **All xAI shares repurchased to date have been retired.**\nThis retirement removes the shares from circulation and reduces the company's outstanding equity.\n\n### Key Conclusion\n\nThe documents detail a consistent share repurchase program across 2024-2026, involving billions of dollars. In **early 2026**, there was a major **dual-track repurchase effort**:\n1.  A **$2.4 billion xAI Merger-related buyback** from xAI employees.\n2.  A **$1.9 billion open-market buyback** of SpaceX securities from existing shareholders.\nAll repurchased shares were subsequently retired.",
